.SH NAME
bond_opt_tryset_rtnl \- try to acquire rtnl and call __bond_opt_set
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" bond_opt_tryset_rtnl
.BI "(struct bonding *bond "  ","
.BI "unsigned int option "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bond" 12
target bond device
.IP "option" 12
option to set
.IP "buf" 12
value to set it to
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function tries to acquire RTNL without blocking and if successful
calls __bond_opt_set. It is mainly used for sysfs option manipulation.
